the keys will disappear when you zone, and you cant bind or CoH here. <br><br>This is also going to be expensive.  We're talking in the range of 400-600pp a person.  While it's only 50pp per person for the port stone, over 3 days you can pretty much say everyone will spend about 150pp per person on reagents like peri's.  Also we will need at least 1-2 coffins per person at 150pp a shot.  Thats why I say its expensive.<br><br>Limited Seating.  48 people.  Max.  Thats it.  No more.<br><br>Stratagy.  We'll take 24 people up the first day to get keys.  They'll camp out and call it a night sometime on Friday.  Probably about 8pm or so.  Log an alt if you want to play EQ more.  On Saturday, bright and early, we'll take everyone else or 24 people again.  The first island will have repop'd and we'll rekill the mobs for 24 more keys.  Thats why we're limited to 48 people.  On the second island we'll send the 24 people who will get keys here across.  The other 24 will duel and be summoned across and revived there.  We'll kill then move to the 4th island, probably on Sunday.  At the 4th island are the flying horses.  These suckers split after you kill them, they're mean, they're cute, and they are unmezable and will kick your butt if your not careful.  Thats why we need ALL 48 people even on Sunday.  If we're short we'll get slaughtered here.<br><br>Necessary people.  Clerics.  Lots of them.  We'll need to camp 1 cleric before we begin killing on the island.  Its not exactly standard procedure, but with the keys the way they are, if we wipeout without one camped, we are totally screwed.  So we'll need like 4 or 5 clerics to be safe.  Necro's, at least 1 high level one who can use the stackable coffins to summon corpses.  While a lower level one will do, the regular coffins both take up lots of space and are bulky.  Tanks.  Lots.<br><br>Now if your asking yourself if its worth it, go to Allakhazam's and take a look at the PoA quests for your class.  You do the math.  Also many people's epic pieces drop here.  We'll try to get some as well.<br><br>I'm not going to gaurntee anything here folks.  I'll sign us up on the KGC board and we'll see.  If not enough people show up, I wont hesitate to cancel the raid.  We cannot be marginal on this one folks.  Either we have enough to kickass and take names, or we dont go.  Also normal alliance restrictions will probably be lifted in this case since PoA is a different matter from the other planes.  Bumps will be handled differently if necessary.<br><br>You must be ready to go on the first day even if you are not picked for to be among the first 24.  I'll need exact numbers or we cant go.  I wont waste people's time or money on the first island just to find out that no one will show on the second day.<br><br>Quest Items.  Handled a bit differently from most other people.  If you can use it, roll.  You can only win 1 piece till everyone in your class has won something.  This is a bit unfair since all the quests need 3 peices to complete it, but its easier than the paperwork involved in other methods.  That might change if this goes off successfully, but for now thats it I think.  Subject to change on the actual sign-up list of course.<br><br>Once again, this is NOT a sign-up.<br><br>Once again, this is NOT a sign-up.<br><br>I do NOT want to see people saying they want to go on this in this thread.  This thread is only for questions pertaining to strategy or specific PoA questions.  I dont want to clutter it up.  I will post a seperate thread on sign-ups if/when we get the dates settled.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>KCoG Plane Raid Liason <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwarriorrmog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorRmog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/1/01 8:47:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard