 same as anywhere else.  Set up camp on an island, send monk sacrafice out, monk brings back a pull or two, group slaughters them or gets slaughtered.  The only tricky part is CR, but as long as you have a cleric camped its not too hard.  I apologize if I gave the impression PoA is some massively hard and difficult zone.  It really is no harder or easier than any other 46+ zone out there.  However, some things dont work and I want people to be prepared.  <br><br>The major hard part is the expense (400-600pp a person) and the time commitment.  Once you are there, your there.  There's no quick rez runs in WC, no quick reagent pickups in EC, no I have to go to a family picnic I'll be back in 5 hours.  Either you can be there uninterrupted for the 3 days, or you cant be and dont go.  Thats something thats very hard for a group like CoG to pull off.  Personally I wouldnt even by trying if Zellex hadnt asked for it.  *shrug*  I suppose its worth a try.<br><br>Dunno if this helped any, but if it didnt, keep asking till it does.  Heh.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>KCoG Plane Raid Liason <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxalos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xalos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/1/01 9:59:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible PoA</span><hr size=1> Here's the rest, still shows the old quest results but the quest drops are the same. Reposted since graffe's have'n site problems.<br>Here's the link at graffe's, More wizard specific stuff for the quests if you can get the site to pull up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!-